  <Section id="research" title="Research">
    <p>
      My research interests include <strong>Multimodal remote sensing, Spatiotemporal analysis, Process-based modeling, and Explainable AI. </strong> 
    </p>
    <p class="meta"><img src="/research.png" alt="research" class="center-image" /></p>      
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Multimodal remote sensing:</strong> Processing, assimilating, and analyzing multispectral,
          hyperspectral, SAR, LIDAR data from satellies, drones, ground-based sensors, and/or in situ measurements.</li>
        <li><strong>Spatiotemporal analysis:</strong> Examining patterns, relationships,
           or trends in data that vary over locations (space) and moments (time) by statistical and geographical methods.</li>
        <li><strong>Process-based modeling:</strong> Leveraging equations or rules to represent real-world processes
           (e.g., photosynthesis, evapotranspiration) to explains and predicts
           how variables change over time by using known physical, biological, or chemical laws, rather than just patterns in data.</li>
        <li><strong>Explainable AI:</strong> Adopting more reasonable and trustworthy domain knowledge (i.e., a black box to a grey box even to a transparent fish tank) to help debug, improve, or regulate AI models
        and help users to understand why AI made a certain decision or prediction.</li>
      </ul>
